  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Data Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain and ensure accurate and timely updates of\ntonnage/cargo lists for both the vessel markets.</li><li>Provide regular market intelligence, research insights, and\nupdates to support client engagement and decision-making.</li><li>Review and validate daily and weekly reports to ensure data\nintegrity, consistency, and accuracy.</li><li>Perform data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL)\nfrom multiple data sources to support various analytical and research projects.</li><li>Review SQL queries and tables to ensure database accuracy,\nreliability, and proper data structure.</li><li>Collaborate closely with the main research desk to align\nmarket views, analysis, and forecasts.</li><li>Develop and maintain forecasting models to assess market\nvolumes and trends.</li><li>Continuously review reports and dashboards to ensure they\nremain relevant, accurate, and aligned with evolving market conditions.</li><li>Support brokers in the negotiation and fixing of vessels,\nproviding timely market information and operational assistance throughout the\ndeal process.</li><li>Update and maintain comprehensive market information,\nactively gathering market intelligence to support commercial decisions.</li><li>Prepare presentation materials and deliver market briefings\nto clients when required.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements :</strong></p><ul><li>Articulate with good inter-personal skills.</li><li>Data and Information analytical skills</li><li>Proficient in SQL and Microsoft Excel</li><li>Basic knowledge in Python or any coding language will be\nadvantageous  </li><li>Possess strong communication skills and customer oriented.</li><li>Able to work independently</li><li>Self-motivated and driven</li><li>Knowledge on international trade, commodities and shipping\nis not necessary but will be advantageous. </li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
